# 📚 Book Sales and Ratings – Exploratory Data Analysis

This project explores and analyzes a dataset of over 1,000 books, focusing on sales performance, user ratings, author reputation, language distribution, and publisher revenue. 
The data was sourced from Kaggle and offers insights into how various factors influence a book's commercial and critical success.

## 🔗 Dataset
- [Kaggle Dataset: Book Sales and Ratings](https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/thedevastator/books-sales-and-ratings)

---

## 📌 Objective

Perform Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) to:
- Clean and prepare the dataset
- Understand book sales trends and user ratings
- Visualize relationships across key variables (e.g., price vs. units sold)
- Identify top-performing authors and publishers
- Analyze genre and language impact on book performance

---

## 🛠️ Tools & Libraries Used

- **Python**  
- **Pandas** – Data manipulation  
- **NumPy** – Numerical computations  
- **Matplotlib & Seaborn** – Data visualization  
- **Jupyter Notebook** – Code development environment

---

## 📊 Key Insights

- 📈 Books published post-2000 tend to have higher unit sales and better ratings.
- ⭐ Top-rated authors include **J.R.R. Tolkien**, **George R.R. Martin**, and **Bill Watterson**.
- 💰 **Penguin Group (USA)** and **Random House LLC** dominate in publisher revenue.
- 📦 Fiction is the most represented genre; English is the most common language.
- 📉 No strong correlation between book price and units sold, suggesting other factors drive demand.

---

## Visualizations

- 📌 Genre distribution via bar chart
- 📌 Unit Sold vs Sale Price (scatter plot)
- 📌 Average Rating per Author (sorted)
- 📌 Publisher revenue analysis (bar plot)
- 📌 Box plot: Units sold vs Author Rating
- 📌 Language distribution via pie chart
